column5: Nothing huge but it beats the dinks I've been getting previously.  Lost another good one at the hole, not great for a whole day out but at least the weather was nice.  Still 2 ices in some parts of the lake, this winter weather is getting ridiculous.  Still having difficulty really nailing them though - I've been out a few times and get the odd bite, but it's nothing like I read about.  Don't know if I'm just hitting the bad days since the setups seem really standard.  Oh yeah, and the dogs got to the tail before I got the camera - fish came out undeformed
Good job man, I wish I got into some that big last week. I ended up with 5 dinks in 4 hours.
Dude, that's a tank!  You're right about splake fishing not being the slam-fest that some articles/people would have you believe, but you usually end up in a pretty spot while doing it.
Nice catch,,I've yet to bag One.
Good one Dan. Nice dark-hued fish there.  That would be my PB as well, had I caught it!
Nice job Dan!  Healthy looking fish.
Good fish dood!  And great pic!  Congrats on the PB!
